-for-seniors-youtube";s:5:"title";s:16:"Pin On Exercises";s:3:"alt";s:16:"pin on exercises";s:3:"url";s:71:"https://i.pinimg.com/736x/20/71/b0/2071b08a8f7cd463624a75943e8a5fbb.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQzOD9nBecVB6x77FXPc4A-EnSDMEyEnMS9lA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:1188;s:6:"height";i:736;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/411375747221175542/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:43:{i:0;s:31:"18 Chair Exercises for Seniors.";i:1;s:53:"A seated workout encompasses far more than movements.";i:2;s:89:"Chair based exercises will develop your cardio fitness muscular strength and flexibility.";i:3;s:54:"Here are some of the best chair exercises for seniors.";i:4;s:116:"Practice these basic movements and choose one or two exercises from each category for a well-rounded seated workout.";i:5;s:127:"Planks can be modified to a simple chair exercise for seniors so as to make the exercise more accessible by the elderly people.";i:6;s:43:"It develops the core strength and mobility.";i:7;s:167:"Place the chair in the front of a wall in a way that the chair is still and stable and it doesnt slide or move from its place while performing the modified plank move.";i:8;s:144:"Simple stretching while laying on the bed move different parts of the body and stretch stiff muscles this can be done assisted or independently.";i:9;s:94:"Chair stretches Here is a great Head to Toe seated chair exercise for Seniors that focuses on.";i:10;s:25:"The worst core exercises.";i:11;s:98:"In the old days sit-ups and crunches were the go-to moves to keep your core muscles in good shape.";i:12;s:61:"But those exercises are not as effective as we once believed.";i:13;s:72:"They strengthen only a few muscles and they pose risks for older adults.";i:14;s:63:"Theyre dangerous because youre pulling on your neck Boehm says.";i:15;s:56:"10 Min Chair Workout For Seniors Hasfit Seated Exercise.";i:16;s:68:"10 minute seated exercises for seniors elderly older people channel.";i:17;s:91:"Bob and brad demonstrate a ten minute seated exercises for seniors elderly or older people.";i:18;s:71:"This week we are giving away a set of bob brad wall anchors plus their.";i:19;s:201:"Exercise 4 Chair Marching First check your posture Lift alternate legs so that your feet lift about 2 inches from the floor and swing your arms forwards and back at a speed that is comfortable for you.";i:20;s:43:"Imagine you marching along at a brisk pace.";i:21;s:33:"Continue for about 20 30 seconds.";i:22;s:74:"Oct 1 2021 - Explore cm roys board senior exercise printable on Pinterest.";i:23;s:56:"See more ideas about exercise senior fitness chair yoga.";i:24;s:47:"Chair Planks are excellent abdominal exercises.";i:25;s:152:"If you are keen on adding substantial strength to your cores inner muscles especially your transverse abdominals as a senior you should consider planks.";i:26;s:94:"Admittedly there is a bit of work in targeting those specific muscles as they wrap your spine.";i:27;s:37:"To get this exercise right we need a.";i:28;s:102:"The only equipment youll need is a chair and then either a couple of water bottles or light dumbbells.";i:29;s:107:"Warm Up Upright Row External Rotation Press Push Pull Side Step Arm Circle Hamstring Stretch Upright Twist.";i:30;s:49:"30 Min Exercise for Seniors and Limited Mobility.";i:31;s:38:"Complete each movement for 50 seconds.";i:32;s:28:"Typewriters Seated Curl Low.";i:33;s:71:"The 17 minute chair workout is perfect for seniors and beginners alike.";i:34;s:67:"HASfits chair exercise for seniors is great for both men and women.";i:35;s:115:"The senior exercises for the elderly only requires a chair and either a couple water bottles or light hand weights.";i:36;s:181:"Chair-bound exercises are ideal for people with lower body injuries or disabilities those with weight problems or diabetes and frail seniors looking to reduce their risk of falling.";i:37;s:158:"Cardiovascular and flexibility chair exercises can help improve posture and reduce back pain while any chair exercise can help alleviate body sores caused by.";i:38;s:77:"Exercise helps you continue to do many of the things you love and need to do.";i:39;s:96:"Many seniors are afraid to exercise at home because they are worried they may injure themselves.";i:40;s:24:"That is a valid concern.";i:41;s:67:"Exercise is meant to improve your health not cause you to get hurt.";i:42;s:78:"As always check with your physician before starting any new exercise programs.";}}